d. } { [%clk 1:16:55] } 20. b4 { [%clk 1:06:20] } 20... axb3 { [%clk 1:15:41] } 21. axb3 { [%clk 1:06:15] } 21... Qb8! { [%cal Gb8b6] [%clk 0:56:57] } 22. c4 { [%clk 1:05:10] } 22... Qb6 { [%clk 0:55:46] } 23. Nf5 { [%clk 0:57:46] } 23... Rfe8 { [%clk 0:53:22] } 24. N3h4 { [%clk 0:39:51] } 24... b4! { Giri proceeds with capturing the a-file by Ra3 and Rea8. } { [%clk 0:47:25] } 25. Kh2 { [%clk 0:33:56] } 25... Ra3 { [%clk 0:43:06] } 26. Rab1 { [%clk 0:33:51] } 26... Ra2 { [%clk 0:37:09] } 27. Qd1 { [%clk 0:18:48] } 27... Nxh4 { [%clk 0:33:51] } 28. Nxh4 { [%clk 0:18:45] } 28... Rea8 { [%clk 0:33:42] } 29. Re2 { [%clk 0:16:41] } 29... Qa7 { [%clk 0:23:54] } 30. Rc1 { [%clk 0:15:22] } 30... Qb6 { [%clk 0:20:24] } 31. Nf3 { [%clk 0:13:45] } 31... h6 { [%clk 0:18:10] } 32. Ne1 { [%clk 0:10:19] } 32... Kh7 { [%clk 0:12:55] } 33. Rxa2 { [%clk 0:06:52] } 33... Rxa2 { [%clk 0:12:53] } 34. Nc2? { Perhaps this is the only move that might be considered as a serious mistake, after which White is close to lose. } { [%clk 0:06:47] } (34. Rc2! Ra3 35. c5! dxc5 36. Nd3 $13 { and White is still in the race. }) 34... Be8! { Great move! Black activates the bishop and highlights a lame disposition of White's pieces. } { [%csl Rc1,Rc2,Rd1,Ge8][%cal Ge8g6] [%clk 0:09:52] } 35. Qd3 { [%clk 0:05:59] } 35... Bg6 { [%clk 0:09:19] } 36. Ra1?! { [%clk 0:03:36] } 36... Rxa1?! { [%clk 0:04:20] } (36... Rb2! { It was stronger, White is absolutely helpless }) 37. Nxa1 { [%clk 0:03:33] } 37... c5?! { After this option, White had a great chance for a draw, but Caruana didn't take the advantage. But I must say that it's not easy to find this option. } { [%clk 0:04:12] } 38. Kg3?? { Fabiano is missing a lucky strike. Now the game ends very quickly. } { [%clk 0:01:53] } (38. dxc6! Qxc6 39. Nc2 Bxe4 40. Nxb4 Qb7 41. Qxd6 Bxg2 42. Nd5 Be4 43. Qe6!! { [%cal Gd5f6] } 43... Qxb3 44. Nxf6+ gxf6 45. Qf7+) 38... Qa7 { [%clk 0:02:51] } 39. Qb1 { [%clk 0:01:17] } 39... h5 { [%clk 0:01:16] } 40. Kf3 { [%clk 0:31:41] } 40... h4 { [%clk 0:30:45] } 41. Kg4 { [%clk 0:18:13] } 41... Qe7 { [%clk 0:29:49] } 42. Qd3 { This move loses immediately, but in any case, White's position cannot be saved. } { [%clk 0:18:38] } 42... f5+! { [%clk 0:23:50] } 43. exf5 { [%clk 0:19:04] } 43... Kh6 { The second brilliant positional achievement of the Dutch grandmaster. Will he be able to impose a fight for the first place? } { [%clk 0:24:04] } 0-1


